(To Mr. Dawn)

35
00:03:37,689 --> 00:03:41,330
Mr. Dawn, the two
weren't able to meet,

36
00:03:42,229 --> 00:03:44,530
but maybe it was for the best.

37
00:03:44,530 --> 00:03:48,669
Maybe I shouldn't have
gotten involved at all.

38
00:03:54,939 --> 00:03:57,009
I wonder what their story is.

39
00:04:22,629 --> 00:04:24,199
(External input)

40
00:04:28,540 --> 00:04:32,439
Mr. Lee Han Seok
traveling to Alberta.

41
00:04:33,310 --> 00:04:35,149
Mr. Lee Han Seok.

42
00:04:35,149 --> 00:04:36,209
Excuse me.

43
00:04:36,209 --> 00:04:39,350
Please come to Gate 7
on the 4th floor...

44
00:04:39,350 --> 00:04:41,420
near the M elevator.

45
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:50,360
Hey.

46
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:52,459
Where are you?

47
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:54,870
I'm at...

48
00:04:55,899 --> 00:04:57,800
Okin-dong in Jongno-gu.

49
00:05:57,829 --> 00:05:59,000
It's Ha Won.

50
00:06:13,310 --> 00:06:15,509
This is the address?

51
00:06:16,509 --> 00:06:17,550
Yes.

52
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,550
What is this place?

53
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:21,519
When we talked,

54
00:06:21,519 --> 00:06:23,759
I noticed the address on the wall.

55
00:06:25,519 --> 00:06:27,189
Doesn't it look so sweet?

56
00:06:27,860 --> 00:06:29,089
A typical Korean house.

57
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,199
Since when were you in Seoul?

58
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,100
I wasn't.

59
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:38,970
Where are you coming from?

60
00:06:40,269 --> 00:06:42,240
- A lecture.
- You flew in from the US?

61
00:06:42,370 --> 00:06:45,110
You wanted to see me,
so I left during a lecture.

62
00:06:55,819 --> 00:06:57,759
It sounds like important news.

63
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,819
Let's get some fresh air first.

64
00:07:00,689 --> 00:07:01,889
I'm okay now.

65
00:07:01,889 --> 00:07:04,160
Still, you should be careful.
Your mom will tell me off.

66
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,300
It's really okay.

67
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:07,930
There's a park. Let's go there.

68
00:07:17,009 --> 00:07:18,879
Your mom always used to say,

69
00:07:19,879 --> 00:07:22,009
"Ha Won can't live in Seoul."

70
00:07:22,009 --> 00:07:23,819
"He'll get rashes all over
and can't survive."

71
00:07:24,620 --> 00:07:26,350
"He must live close to trees."

72
00:07:27,319 --> 00:07:30,189
That was when I was young.
I'm totally fine now.

73
00:07:35,029 --> 00:07:37,259
Say what you want to say.
You said it's important.

74
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,360
Why the rush?

75
00:07:41,170 --> 00:07:43,399
"What would Korea be like with you?"

76
00:07:43,399 --> 00:07:45,500
"Korea... Korea..."

77
00:07:46,439 --> 00:07:49,970
We only imagined it
and now we're both here.

78
00:07:50,910 --> 00:07:52,040
Let's take our time.

79
00:07:54,550 --> 00:07:55,680
Are you free?

80
00:07:56,610 --> 00:07:57,649
Yes.

81
00:07:58,819 --> 00:08:01,120
- Shall we go there?
- You want to go somewhere?

82
00:08:02,149 --> 00:08:03,519
The place you wanted to go to.

83
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,360
Me?

84
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:13,800
"A single leaf, without a sound,"

85
00:08:15,170 --> 00:08:17,740
"landed softly on my shoulder."

86
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:22,540
"The universe
put a hand on my body."

87
00:08:23,470 --> 00:08:24,639
"It's so light."

88
00:08:26,139 --> 00:08:27,410
"Misiryeong Valley Sunset".

89
00:08:34,250 --> 00:08:35,720
It's beautiful.

90
00:08:55,070 --> 00:08:57,070
Ha Won. Look over there.

91
00:09:03,450 --> 00:09:05,820
It's a place we only imagined.

92
00:09:07,250 --> 00:09:09,419
I'm so glad we came here together.

93
00:09:13,059 --> 00:09:14,389
Now I can tell you.

94
00:09:35,049 --> 00:09:36,250
I'm getting married.

95
00:09:51,799 --> 00:09:55,330
(A Piece of Your Mind)

96
00:09:56,929 --> 00:09:58,539
So what? She ran away?

97
00:10:00,039 --> 00:10:01,940
She didn't exactly run away.

98
00:10:01,940 --> 00:10:05,080
It's the same thing.
Why did she run away?

99
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:07,139
She fell out of love and dumped him.

100
00:10:07,139 --> 00:10:08,909
My gosh. I don't believe it.

101
00:10:12,620 --> 00:10:14,350
Ji Su dumped him?

102
00:10:15,919 --> 00:10:18,389
I'll plant a cluster of herbs here,

103
00:10:18,389 --> 00:10:20,220
and when I have guests,

104
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:22,529
- I'll make them tea.
- You'll never tell me.

105
00:10:27,799 --> 00:10:30,470
After he broke up with Ji Su,
he told me...

106
00:10:31,970 --> 00:10:33,139
I couldn't believe it.

107
00:10:38,139 --> 00:10:41,080
When my grandma
was a diplomat, she said...

108
00:10:41,350 --> 00:10:43,450
sometimes the Korean expats
are victimized.

109
00:10:43,450 --> 00:10:47,179
She felt a lot of guilt about
not being able to help them.

110
00:10:47,179 --> 00:10:48,590
Things are different now.

111
00:10:48,850 --> 00:10:51,419
Anyway, for reasons similar to that,

112
00:10:51,419 --> 00:10:54,690
Ha Won ended up on his own
and Grandma brought him over.

113
00:10:55,289 --> 00:10:56,789
That's how he became my uncle.

114
00:10:56,990 --> 00:10:59,129
- I told you before, right?
- The really smart guy.

115
00:11:01,230 --> 00:11:03,029
The first time I met the kid...

116
00:11:03,529 --> 00:11:05,139
The two of us are friends.

117
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:07,200
I call him uncle and by his name.

118
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:09,210
I call him lots of things,
but it's the same guy.

119
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,159
He was in a lecture in the US,

120
00:11:29,159 --> 00:11:32,000
but he got a call from Ji Su
and boarded a plane.

121
00:11:33,259 --> 00:11:35,899
He came to Seoul then
and hasn't left since.

122
00:11:36,070 --> 00:11:37,230
Where is this place?

123
00:11:42,009 --> 00:11:44,080
(47-435 Okin-dong, Jongno-gu)

124
00:12:15,070 --> 00:12:16,070
Uncle?

125
00:12:17,539 --> 00:12:18,580
Sun Ho.

126
00:12:19,309 --> 00:12:23,250
I witnessed the beginning of
the persistent unrequited love.

127
00:12:23,809 --> 00:12:26,049
Oh, that place was that address.

128
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:29,220
What's wrong with you?

129
00:12:29,490 --> 00:12:32,019
Why did that make me so sad?

130
00:12:35,090 --> 00:12:36,730
Where did you live?

131
00:12:37,330 --> 00:12:38,659
That question is blocked.

132
00:12:41,230 --> 00:12:43,399
What does that
have to do with research?

133
00:12:44,299 --> 00:12:45,600
Where did you stay with Kim Ji Su?

134
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,809
Oslo. Seoul.

135
00:12:49,110 --> 00:12:50,110
Gangneung.

136
00:12:51,679 --> 00:12:53,639
When did you
go to Gangneung with Ji Su?

137
00:12:54,279 --> 00:12:55,679
We broke up there,

138
00:12:55,679 --> 00:12:57,620
and I stayed there alone
for a few months.

139
00:12:57,620 --> 00:13:00,379
- What year was that?
- 2013.

140
00:13:00,889 --> 00:13:02,720
2013?

141
00:13:03,549 --> 00:13:05,720
It was when we were
developing the GPS tracker.

142
00:13:06,090 --> 00:13:08,360
Where did you live
is a blocked question,

143
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:10,490
but when I ask where you stayed
with Ji Su,

144
00:13:10,490 --> 00:13:11,629
you spilled everything.

145
00:13:11,629 --> 00:13:12,730
you spilled everything.

146
00:13:17,169 --> 00:13:18,769
If I mention Ji Su,

147
00:13:18,769 --> 00:13:21,210
it'll answer any question.
Isn't that weird?

148
00:13:21,610 --> 00:13:23,370
I think it's related to
the trigger point.

149
00:13:23,370 --> 00:13:24,809
Change the password setting.

150
00:13:25,210 --> 00:13:26,379
Are there any other issues?

151
00:13:26,379 --> 00:13:28,580
None if it's not your device.

152
00:13:28,909 --> 00:13:31,250
We'll train it with
virtual patients,

153
00:13:31,250 --> 00:13:33,919
improve the accuracy,
then share it with the hospital.

154
00:13:33,919 --> 00:13:35,220
We need to test this...

155
00:13:35,220 --> 00:13:37,120
with real patients
for better accuracy.

156
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:38,289
So...

157
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:40,490
this should be scrapped.

158
00:13:41,389 --> 00:13:44,500
Let's end the unofficial tests
that we've kept to ourselves.

159
00:13:55,470 --> 00:13:56,639
- What?
- What?

160
00:13:59,340 --> 00:14:02,009
Well... I always talked
to that thing.

161
00:14:02,049 --> 00:14:05,049
And it responded
to all the nonsense I said.

162
00:14:05,980 --> 00:14:08,320
I feel a little sad...

163
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:11,320
thinking that I'll no longer
be able to talk to it.

164
00:14:16,789 --> 00:14:17,960
What?

165
00:14:21,399 --> 00:14:22,769
It's for therapy.

166
00:14:23,370 --> 00:14:24,799
Yes, it's for therapy.

167
00:14:38,049 --> 00:14:39,419
What do you think, Seo Woo?

168
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:41,620
I like it.

169
00:14:42,149 --> 00:14:43,419
Why don't you mix it yourself?

170
00:14:43,990 --> 00:14:44,990
What?

171
00:14:44,990 --> 00:14:47,190
But I'm not...

172
00:14:47,559 --> 00:14:49,059
You need to practice to improve.

173
00:14:49,559 --> 00:14:52,360
You have good ears,
so I'm sure you'll do well.

174
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,470
Thank you.

175
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:59,139
It's weird to see everyone here.

176
00:14:59,539 --> 00:15:02,169
Everyone here including myself
used to be the original members.

177
00:15:02,470 --> 00:15:04,279
What did you hear
from the recording studio?

178
00:15:04,279 --> 00:15:05,940
Hasn't anyone told you anything yet?

179
00:15:05,940 --> 00:15:07,279
No, not yet.

180
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:12,049
We're planning to record this week.

181
00:15:12,049 --> 00:15:13,049
And?

182
00:15:13,850 --> 00:15:15,490
You can come by
and take a look if you want.

183
00:15:15,490 --> 00:15:17,590
It's a small studio,
but the sound comes out great.

184
00:15:17,860 --> 00:15:19,159
You'll learn a few things.

185
00:15:20,590 --> 00:15:21,690
Right.

186
00:15:22,629 --> 00:15:23,730
(To Mr. Dawn, the two
weren't able to meet,)

187
00:15:23,730 --> 00:15:24,860
(but maybe it was for the best.)

188
00:15:28,370 --> 00:15:30,700
I wonder if Mr. Dawn
no longer comes here.

189
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:40,980
Excuse me.

190
00:15:47,990 --> 00:15:49,590
She told you
that her life is miserable?

191
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:51,960
Her life was miserable,
but she refused to talk to him.

192
00:15:52,090 --> 00:15:53,889
So that means her life is miserable.

193
00:15:59,059 --> 00:16:01,330
I'm going to stop getting involved.

194
00:16:03,970 --> 00:16:06,039
You can drink if you want.
I don't drink.

195
00:16:06,039 --> 00:16:07,539
No, it's okay.

196
00:16:09,769 --> 00:16:12,610
I feel bad for that guy
named Ha Won.

197
00:16:13,139 --> 00:16:15,110
I don't get
why you feel bad for him.

198
00:16:15,179 --> 00:16:16,779
He's just like me.

199
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:19,919
How so?

200
00:16:19,919 --> 00:16:22,350
He believes in something
that's not even there.

201
00:16:22,490 --> 00:16:24,590
I'm really good at doing that.

202
00:16:25,190 --> 00:16:28,559
I do my best to get what I want,
dream of things,

203
00:16:28,559 --> 00:16:30,289
overanalyze all the time,

204
00:16:30,289 --> 00:16:33,200
and use up a lot of my affection,
time, and sincerity.

205
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:35,500
But he stood strong
for over 10 years.

206
00:16:36,370 --> 00:16:38,139
Who likes someone
for that long these days?

207
00:16:38,139 --> 00:16:40,039
These days,
people compete with love.

208
00:16:40,039 --> 00:16:41,669
People always fight about
who loves whom more.

209
00:16:41,669 --> 00:16:45,309
Love is unmeasurable, but people
are always busy measuring things.

210
00:16:46,679 --> 00:16:49,809
But on the other hand,
he just wants a piece of her.

211
00:16:51,580 --> 00:16:53,320
He told you a lot of things.

212
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:56,620
I wonder how he managed
to keep liking her for 10 years.

213
00:16:57,090 --> 00:16:58,220
I'm so curious.

214
00:17:01,429 --> 00:17:03,490
Wouldn't it be possible
if someone's that precious?

215
00:17:06,759 --> 00:17:10,430
I think it's possible if that person
is what keeps you grounded.

216
00:17:12,769 --> 00:17:15,809
Just a few words are enough
to keep people grounded.

217
00:17:20,210 --> 00:17:22,109
"Just a few words".

218
00:17:23,410 --> 00:17:27,119
If I hear something I want to hear,
I think that will enable me...

219
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:30,089
to keep going
for about three more years.

220
00:17:30,549 --> 00:17:32,460
But no one's ever said it to me.

221
00:17:35,289 --> 00:17:36,660
"I want you to stay."

222
00:17:37,930 --> 00:17:40,460
The realtor called me
numerous times...

223
00:17:40,460 --> 00:17:42,299
and asked me to sell
the semi-basement room.

224
00:17:42,299 --> 00:17:45,299
If it weren't for you,
I would've sold it right away.

225
00:17:46,269 --> 00:17:47,970
"Seo Woo."

226
00:17:48,839 --> 00:17:50,140
"I want you to stay."

227
00:17:50,140 --> 00:17:51,480
I'll be off now.

228
00:17:51,480 --> 00:17:53,279
Okay. Bye, Seo Woo.

229
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:56,079
The cello doesn't sound right.
Do you hear that?

230
00:17:56,079 --> 00:17:57,579
- "Seo Woo."
- You're right.

231
00:17:58,150 --> 00:17:59,519
"I want you to stay."

232
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:13,700
I wonder what Ha Won will do next.

233
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,730
He probably won't do anything.

234
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:20,440
Really? Are you sure?

235
00:18:21,069 --> 00:18:24,579
(Rice)

236
00:19:13,559 --> 00:19:14,990
I heard you're miserable.

237
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:31,940
I heard you're miserable.

238
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:42,420
I heard you're miserable.

239
00:19:44,319 --> 00:19:46,190
You call me in years,

240
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:48,160
and that's what you say to me?

241
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:49,559
I told you to call me.

242
00:19:53,430 --> 00:19:55,569
I could instantly tell from behind
that you're miserable.

243
00:19:55,730 --> 00:19:59,269
Why did you run when you can't
even run that well?

244
00:20:04,579 --> 00:20:06,109
It's been so long.

245
00:20:10,150 --> 00:20:11,579
I'm not miserable.

246
00:20:11,579 --> 00:20:13,150
Then why did you run away?

247
00:20:14,349 --> 00:20:16,420
Because you showed up
out of nowhere.

248
00:20:16,420 --> 00:20:18,119
Then how was I supposed to show up?

249
00:20:24,359 --> 00:20:27,430
Ha Won,
I can't talk to you right now.

250
00:20:28,099 --> 00:20:30,130
- Let's talk next time...
- When?

251
00:20:39,140 --> 00:20:41,039
I'll call you back in 20 minutes.

252
00:20:46,650 --> 00:20:47,650
(Ha Won)

253
00:21:24,990 --> 00:21:26,990
My fiance knows you.

254
00:21:27,220 --> 00:21:28,930
I think he's bothered by you.

255
00:21:29,730 --> 00:21:31,329
Who is he? How does he know me?

256
00:21:32,730 --> 00:21:36,470
We were together
ever since you left.

257
00:21:36,529 --> 00:21:38,640
You met him in Norway?

258
00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:40,940
But I can't think of anyone...

259
00:21:40,940 --> 00:21:42,740
Can you not guess?

260
00:21:43,339 --> 00:21:44,539
Please.

261
00:21:53,150 --> 00:21:54,480
Do you love him?

262
00:21:55,789 --> 00:21:57,019
Well...

263
00:21:57,450 --> 00:22:00,160
I think he turns me
into a better person.

264
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:01,430
We both like
the same kind of music...

265
00:22:01,430 --> 00:22:02,460
So...

266
00:22:05,059 --> 00:22:06,460
do you love him?

267
00:22:08,430 --> 00:22:09,569
Yes.

268
00:22:27,950 --> 00:22:30,750
I hope you respect my decision.

269
00:22:33,420 --> 00:22:34,859
Of course, I respect your decision.

270
00:22:36,789 --> 00:22:37,960
But...

271
00:22:41,799 --> 00:22:43,430
you can go ahead and get married.

272
00:22:46,140 --> 00:22:48,339
Meanwhile,
I'm going to keep loving you.

273
00:22:51,839 --> 00:22:53,740
My love for you...

274
00:22:53,740 --> 00:22:55,980
won't affect your life
in any kind of way at all.

275
00:22:56,579 --> 00:23:00,319
I promise I won't disturb you.
So don't worry...

276
00:23:04,819 --> 00:23:06,420
and respect my choice too.

277
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:16,329
I believe you'll have a happy life.

278
00:23:18,799 --> 00:23:19,869
And you should.

279
00:23:22,670 --> 00:23:23,740
But...

280
00:23:26,039 --> 00:23:27,910
do call me when life gets miserable.

281
00:23:44,329 --> 00:23:48,430
(Ji Su)

282
00:23:55,509 --> 00:23:58,380
The voice recording, the bowls,
and the delivery address.

283
00:23:59,309 --> 00:24:00,480
That was all you, wasn't it?

284
00:24:01,710 --> 00:24:02,750
Why though?

285
00:24:03,609 --> 00:24:04,680
It was a message.

286
00:24:10,349 --> 00:24:11,690
I was reminding you...

287
00:24:12,859 --> 00:24:14,390
to call me if you're miserable.

288
00:24:15,829 --> 00:24:17,289
I was going to do this
every 10 years,

289
00:24:17,289 --> 00:24:18,859
but I caught you on my first try.

290
00:24:20,029 --> 00:24:21,130
That again?

291
00:24:22,470 --> 00:24:25,140
I can't say that
I'm perfectly happy,

292
00:24:26,299 --> 00:24:28,140
but I can't say
that I'm miserable either.

293
00:24:30,210 --> 00:24:33,480
I'm somewhat unhappy
but somewhat in bliss.

294
00:24:33,980 --> 00:24:35,210
You're being cryptic.

295
00:24:38,009 --> 00:24:39,150
Have a good life.

296
00:24:42,549 --> 00:24:44,789
- Ji Su...
- I won't run next time.

297
00:24:45,519 --> 00:24:46,619
Happy now?

298
00:24:48,859 --> 00:24:49,890
Ji Su.

299
00:24:51,759 --> 00:24:53,529
"Ji Su..."

300
00:24:54,700 --> 00:24:56,099
It's been a while
since I heard that.

301
00:25:09,349 --> 00:25:11,880
Ha Won, my life is not that bad,

302
00:25:12,549 --> 00:25:13,619
so don't worry.

303
00:25:22,789 --> 00:25:26,500
I was going to ask you
before throwing it out.

304
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:27,700
Why would you get rid of it?

305
00:25:28,529 --> 00:25:31,500
Put this outside on a rainy day.

306
00:25:31,500 --> 00:25:33,200
That sometimes spruces it up.

307
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:35,869
It's known to enjoy
the sweet taste of rain.

308
00:25:36,009 --> 00:25:37,410
What if someone steals it?

309
00:25:37,410 --> 00:25:38,809
Seriously? It's better than...

310
00:25:38,809 --> 00:25:40,640
throwing it away and letting it die.

311
00:25:42,849 --> 00:25:45,049
- Welcome!
- Do you make deliveries?

312
00:25:45,049 --> 00:25:46,119
Yes, of course.

313
00:25:53,460 --> 00:25:55,130
It's like he doesn't remember me.

314
00:25:59,359 --> 00:26:00,630
Are you looking for
something in particular?

315
00:26:01,900 --> 00:26:04,670
- Something small.
- Check the plants over there.

316
00:26:07,170 --> 00:26:08,640
You can take your time.

317
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:37,500
Hello, this is Han Seo Woo.

318
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:38,700
Yes, Seo Woo.

319
00:26:39,170 --> 00:26:40,740
Is that Seo Woo?

320
00:26:42,170 --> 00:26:43,170
Hello.

321
00:26:44,140 --> 00:26:46,009
I recognized you
the moment you walked in.

322
00:26:46,339 --> 00:26:48,279
- Don't you remember me?
- Hello?

323
00:26:50,410 --> 00:26:51,849
I'm here, go ahead.

324
00:26:51,849 --> 00:26:53,950
The cello sonata recorded...

325
00:26:53,950 --> 00:26:55,750
was confirmed by Mr. Choi.

326
00:26:55,750 --> 00:26:57,420
The file has been sent via email.

327
00:26:58,289 --> 00:26:59,420
I mixed it myself...

328
00:26:59,420 --> 00:27:01,559
and Mr. Choi gave me his approval.

329
00:27:01,660 --> 00:27:03,529
I'd like you to hear it as well.

330
00:27:04,460 --> 00:27:06,460
It's my first, you see.

331
00:27:06,630 --> 00:27:09,000
- Congrats. I'll check it out.
- Congrats on what?

332
00:27:13,539 --> 00:27:15,210
I'll ask her myself
once you hang up.

333
00:27:16,069 --> 00:27:18,410
Someone here wants to call you.

334
00:27:18,410 --> 00:27:19,440
Oh, I see.

335
00:27:20,039 --> 00:27:22,049
Have a good day then.

336
00:27:23,079 --> 00:27:25,420
You hung up already? Now I feel bad.

337
00:27:26,319 --> 00:27:27,450
Han Seo Woo.

338
00:27:32,690 --> 00:27:35,130
Seo Woo, I hear I should
congratulate you on something.

339
00:27:35,990 --> 00:27:37,789
Of course, I know.

340
00:27:38,230 --> 00:27:40,029
The world is a small place.

341
00:27:40,460 --> 00:27:42,829
Could you come here
if you're not too busy?

342
00:27:43,970 --> 00:27:45,400
I'll give you the address.

343
00:27:46,339 --> 00:27:48,509
There's something I want to ask.

344
00:27:48,869 --> 00:27:51,269
Am I allowed to
always be at the studio?

345
00:27:51,980 --> 00:27:53,440
Even when...

346
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:55,910
there is no recording scheduled?
I'm usually always there anyway.

347
00:27:56,809 --> 00:27:57,880
I don't know.

348
00:27:58,819 --> 00:28:00,250
Then give me an answer...

349
00:28:00,250 --> 00:28:03,019
so that I can decide whether or not
to care for the place.

350
00:28:06,660 --> 00:28:08,220
Is that how you usually operate?

351
00:28:08,220 --> 00:28:12,460
Of course. I care for every inch
of the place I work at.

352
00:28:13,359 --> 00:28:15,829
In that case,
your question seems reasonable.

353
00:28:16,299 --> 00:28:17,369
Hold on.

354
00:28:30,609 --> 00:28:31,609
Yes?

355
00:28:35,250 --> 00:28:36,450
Ask her to be there.

356
00:28:37,049 --> 00:28:38,049
Okay.

357
00:28:39,720 --> 00:28:40,789
You're good.

358
00:28:41,589 --> 00:28:42,589
Sorry?

359
00:28:43,460 --> 00:28:44,630
You're to be there.

360
00:28:45,529 --> 00:28:47,430
You're to always be at the studio.

361
00:28:50,900 --> 00:28:53,099
Is it Ha Won who's
giving those orders?

362
00:28:53,339 --> 00:28:55,970
Your world has been revolving
around Ha Won lately, hasn't it?

363
00:28:57,240 --> 00:28:59,539
Well, I've been someone
important to him.

364
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:04,609
As if. He doesn't consider
anyone to be important to him.

365
00:29:06,019 --> 00:29:07,049
Let's head inside.

366
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:25,799
(Ji Su)

367
00:29:36,980 --> 00:29:37,980
Hey.

368
00:29:38,849 --> 00:29:40,950
I was busy doing the laundry
to pick up earlier.

369
00:29:41,549 --> 00:29:42,549
What's up?

370
00:29:43,019 --> 00:29:45,049
You're even doing laundry now?

371
00:29:47,359 --> 00:29:49,589
All I can do is
scoff at those words.

372
00:29:51,490 --> 00:29:52,960
You called for no reason,
didn't you?

373
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:56,400
Yes.

374
00:30:23,259 --> 00:30:24,289
You're here.

375
00:30:42,250 --> 00:30:43,680
(Ji Su)

376
00:30:47,579 --> 00:30:49,650
(Shindongmun Station)

377
00:30:57,529 --> 00:30:59,259
What other messages did you send?

378
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:02,000
Just a second ago,

379
00:31:03,970 --> 00:31:05,869
the sky darkened
and it started to rain.

380
00:31:07,599 --> 00:31:10,140
- Yes.
- That's my message too.

381
00:31:11,670 --> 00:31:13,240
The sun rising and setting,

382
00:31:14,880 --> 00:31:18,210
the wind blowing,
it raining, and everything.

383
00:31:19,650 --> 00:31:22,819
Everything you saw and heard.

384
00:31:24,289 --> 00:31:27,259
That's my message for you
to be happy no matter where you are.

385
00:31:48,339 --> 00:31:49,650
It's from Kang In Wook.

386
00:32:21,039 --> 00:32:23,250
Jin Moo, must the recording
be on the day after tomorrow?

387
00:32:23,250 --> 00:32:25,150
- Yes, probably.
- How many hours do we get?

388
00:32:25,619 --> 00:32:27,880
An hour.
This place isn't easy to book.

389
00:32:31,690 --> 00:32:32,920
Record what I'll be playing.

390
00:32:35,119 --> 00:32:36,190
Han Seo Woo.

391
00:32:37,329 --> 00:32:40,299
Ms. Han, can you turn up
the volume for the piano?

392
00:32:42,329 --> 00:32:43,369
Sure thing.

393
00:32:44,099 --> 00:32:45,099
Find me.

394
00:32:47,869 --> 00:32:50,210
Maybe it wasn't a person talking.

395
00:33:23,670 --> 00:33:24,869
Wait here.

396
00:33:25,910 --> 00:33:27,210
In Wook.

397
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:37,250
If we could apologize...

398
00:33:40,490 --> 00:33:41,720
To whom?

399
00:33:44,490 --> 00:33:45,930
Should we go to Oslo?

400
00:33:46,359 --> 00:33:47,559
Shall we go?

401
00:33:54,599 --> 00:33:56,839
You'll just talk to thin air.
Just say it now.

402
00:34:00,910 --> 00:34:02,380
If I could...

403
00:34:05,619 --> 00:34:07,750
apologize to Ha Won...

404
00:34:11,650 --> 00:34:13,289
You're not in touch anymore.

405
00:34:15,289 --> 00:34:17,130
I have his email address.

406
00:34:17,130 --> 00:34:19,329
- If I call...
- There's nothing to apologize for.

407
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:23,869
It weighs too much on me.

408
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:26,070
I told you already that
it's too much for me.

409
00:34:27,639 --> 00:34:28,670
Ji Su.

410
00:34:28,940 --> 00:34:31,769
It's not a problem
as long as you're okay with it.

411
00:34:31,769 --> 00:34:33,610
The mess we're in now...

412
00:34:37,380 --> 00:34:38,679
No.

413
00:34:40,980 --> 00:34:42,719
It's your problem now.

414
00:35:56,760 --> 00:35:58,289
I saw you come in.

415
00:35:58,789 --> 00:36:00,300
Do you know this place?

416
00:36:00,699 --> 00:36:03,329
It's my favorite cafe.
Isn't it nice here?

417
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:05,400
You were looking at something.

418
00:36:06,469 --> 00:36:08,000
I was people-watching.

419
00:36:08,239 --> 00:36:09,340
I do that a lot.

420
00:36:09,340 --> 00:36:10,510
On your own?

421
00:36:11,469 --> 00:36:13,610
In case someone comes.

422
00:36:14,340 --> 00:36:16,010
I'm so dull-witted.

423
00:36:16,010 --> 00:36:17,780
I'll sit at another table.

424
00:36:18,750 --> 00:36:20,920
I have some good news.

425
00:36:20,920 --> 00:36:23,119
I can come to the recording studio
whenever I want.

426
00:36:23,849 --> 00:36:27,219
Congratulations.
I don't go there anymore.

427
00:36:28,719 --> 00:36:30,159
You're done?

428
00:36:32,860 --> 00:36:35,260
Now in the mornings,
there won't be any coffee, music

429
00:36:36,400 --> 00:36:37,730
or cleaning up to do.

430
00:36:40,739 --> 00:36:42,070
I guess not.

431
00:36:45,170 --> 00:36:46,539
Right here.

432
00:36:47,010 --> 00:36:49,809
This is where Ha Won
failed to meet Ji Su.

433
00:36:49,909 --> 00:36:51,949
And I almost saw him.

434
00:36:55,889 --> 00:36:59,260
Is there something
you want to ask Ha Won?

435
00:37:01,820 --> 00:37:03,130
No.

436
00:37:03,829 --> 00:37:06,059
I just want to see him from afar.

437
00:37:07,400 --> 00:37:08,630
From afar?

438
00:37:09,829 --> 00:37:12,070
His full face. From afar.

439
00:37:13,170 --> 00:37:14,369
Why from afar?

440
00:37:14,369 --> 00:37:17,809
If we're close,
he'll see that I pity him.

441
00:37:20,280 --> 00:37:21,710
The look on my face.

442
00:37:22,980 --> 00:37:25,480
I just want to see
what he looks like.

443
00:37:25,480 --> 00:37:27,920
A guy who looks like that
went through that.

444
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:31,119
I just want to see his face.
Why would I ask him anything?

445
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:34,860
You should work at the studio that
wants you to stay for a long time.

446
00:37:39,030 --> 00:37:40,030
Okay.

447
00:37:44,869 --> 00:37:46,300
You can stay here.

448
00:37:46,300 --> 00:37:48,369
You said you're waiting for someone.

449
00:37:49,170 --> 00:37:50,269
I doubt they'll come.

450
00:37:50,269 --> 00:37:52,409
They must. I can sit...

451
00:37:54,380 --> 00:37:57,309
I have many other favorite cafes.
I'll go somewhere else.

452
00:38:15,260 --> 00:38:18,030
I feel rotten to know
I won't see him again.

453
00:38:39,860 --> 00:38:41,119
Ha Won.

454
00:38:42,489 --> 00:38:44,329
Shall we go to Norway?

455
00:38:52,869 --> 00:38:54,000
When?

456
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:55,840
Tomorrow works.

457
00:38:58,010 --> 00:38:59,139
Why?

458
00:38:59,809 --> 00:39:01,880
I need your help.

459
00:39:03,179 --> 00:39:05,480
I need you to do something there.

460
00:39:08,980 --> 00:39:10,119
What?

461
00:39:12,389 --> 00:39:14,760
You just have to say one thing.

462
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:16,230
What one thing?

463
00:39:17,090 --> 00:39:18,530
I'll say it now.

464
00:39:21,099 --> 00:39:22,630
It's...

465
00:39:22,630 --> 00:39:24,730
It's fine. Tell me.

466
00:39:25,699 --> 00:39:27,440
I'll hear it first, then help you.

467
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:31,340
I shouldn't have
brought it up. Sorry.

468
00:39:31,869 --> 00:39:34,139
- I'll call you...
- Let's go. Tomorrow.

469
00:39:36,650 --> 00:39:38,409
I'll help first, then listen.

470
00:39:41,280 --> 00:39:43,849
Okay. Let's meet at that cafe.

471
00:39:43,849 --> 00:39:45,050
I know.

472
00:39:45,860 --> 00:39:47,219
The one you ran away from.

473
00:39:49,989 --> 00:39:52,260
See you there tomorrow morning.

474
00:39:56,030 --> 00:39:57,929
There's nothing to apologize for.

475
00:39:58,269 --> 00:40:01,269
It weighs too much on me.

476
00:40:01,369 --> 00:40:03,639
I told you already that
it's too much for me.

477
00:40:04,969 --> 00:40:06,809
No. Forget it.

478
00:40:06,840 --> 00:40:10,280
I'll call you again in the evening.
I'll think about it some more.

479
00:40:10,280 --> 00:40:12,110
Think about what?

480
00:40:14,719 --> 00:40:16,449
It might be hard for you.

481
00:40:16,449 --> 00:40:17,590
See you tomorrow.

482
00:41:08,769 --> 00:41:10,210
Did you come to the cafe?

483
00:41:11,610 --> 00:41:12,780
Yes.

484
00:41:12,980 --> 00:41:14,710
You can wait inside.

485
00:41:15,980 --> 00:41:17,179
Thank you.

486
00:42:30,650 --> 00:42:31,949
Leave.

487
00:42:33,460 --> 00:42:37,030
I'll stay and find out the reason.

488
00:43:16,929 --> 00:43:19,500
Again, I'm sorry about
what happened that day.

489
00:43:19,739 --> 00:43:21,500
Let me know when you're free.

490
00:43:21,500 --> 00:43:22,769
(To Kim Ji Su. Again, I'm sorry...)

491
00:43:22,769 --> 00:43:24,010
(about what happened that day.
Let me know when you're free.)

492
00:43:24,010 --> 00:43:25,039
(I'm nearby.)

493
00:43:25,039 --> 00:43:26,139
I'm nearby.

494
00:43:36,690 --> 00:43:37,719
Over here.

495
00:43:43,489 --> 00:43:45,489
It's either a gift
or a small burden.

496
00:43:46,329 --> 00:43:48,500
- What is it?
- A plant.

497
00:43:49,059 --> 00:43:50,699
You can keep it
if you know how to take care of it.

498
00:43:50,929 --> 00:43:53,769
If not, you just need to water it
every now and then.

499
00:43:54,000 --> 00:43:55,300
It's a little sensitive.

500
00:43:55,639 --> 00:43:57,269
I'm great at growing plants.

501
00:43:58,170 --> 00:44:00,039
Then it's a gift. You can keep it.

502
00:44:01,079 --> 00:44:02,809
What were you doing nearby?

503
00:44:05,480 --> 00:44:07,179
I needed to make a decision.

504
00:44:08,349 --> 00:44:09,690
I'm going to leave on my own.

505
00:44:10,219 --> 00:44:12,860
I'm a little scared,
but I'm still going to go.

506
00:44:15,519 --> 00:44:18,489
It bothers me a little
to hear that you're scared.

507
00:44:21,730 --> 00:44:23,099
I'll be fine.

508
00:44:23,900 --> 00:44:26,699
I've become a lot more courageous
after having talked to you.

509
00:44:30,340 --> 00:44:31,469
You can tell me more.

510
00:44:31,969 --> 00:44:34,340
I'm ready to listen
to anything you have to say.

511
00:44:35,579 --> 00:44:37,849
You gave me a gift,
so go ahead and tell me whatever.

512
00:44:38,550 --> 00:44:40,619
You can even tell me
what bothers you.

513
00:44:58,500 --> 00:44:59,500
Before...

514
00:45:00,199 --> 00:45:01,900
I met my husband,

515
00:45:03,110 --> 00:45:05,170
something happened to him.

516
00:45:06,380 --> 00:45:08,280
He made a mistake.

517
00:45:11,150 --> 00:45:13,050
And I've been struggling...

518
00:45:14,449 --> 00:45:15,920
ever since I found out.

519
00:45:18,320 --> 00:45:21,389
It turned my entire world
upside down.

520
00:45:24,289 --> 00:45:25,659
I never knew...

521
00:45:27,059 --> 00:45:28,659
how it felt...

522
00:45:31,000 --> 00:45:32,369
to be in torment.

523
00:45:35,599 --> 00:45:36,639
This...

524
00:45:38,070 --> 00:45:39,110
This feeling...

525
00:45:43,909 --> 00:45:45,309
You didn't go
to the mountains, did you?

526
00:45:45,550 --> 00:45:47,449
I told you to go somewhere high.

527
00:45:47,820 --> 00:45:49,920
It really helps
to look down at the view.

528
00:45:50,719 --> 00:45:53,090
You can even shout
at the top of your lungs.

529
00:45:55,190 --> 00:45:57,059
Would you like to shout in there?

530
00:45:57,489 --> 00:46:00,230
It's completely soundproof and
a great way to relieve your stress.

531
00:46:06,070 --> 00:46:08,900
This isn't exactly
what you want to hear, is it?

532
00:46:10,610 --> 00:46:12,809
There's probably something else
that you want to hear.

533
00:46:15,139 --> 00:46:17,550
Something that will
put your mind at ease.

534
00:46:22,250 --> 00:46:23,389
