Even lifeless things fall sometimes.

548
00:48:18,670 --> 00:48:20,940
They're all machines in there.
It's funny that it just fell.

549
00:48:21,699 --> 00:48:23,969
What is this?

550
00:48:25,710 --> 00:48:26,739
This...

551
00:48:29,579 --> 00:48:31,809
I think Mr. Dawn wrote this.

552
00:48:33,420 --> 00:48:35,380
I wonder what his job is.

553
00:48:35,780 --> 00:48:37,219
This is a flowchart.

554
00:48:38,190 --> 00:48:39,250
"Mr. Dawn"?

555
00:48:39,550 --> 00:48:41,159
He rents this place
for four hours at dawn.

556
00:48:41,159 --> 00:48:43,389
So I call him Mr. Dawn.

557
00:48:44,630 --> 00:48:46,500
I actually ran into him yesterday
at the cafe...

558
00:48:46,500 --> 00:48:47,860
that we frequently went to.

559
00:48:48,500 --> 00:48:49,869
He told me he won't be
coming here anymore.

560
00:48:53,000 --> 00:48:55,170
He suddenly called out of nowhere
and asked if I was miserable.

561
00:48:55,570 --> 00:48:56,809
And I was so puzzled.

562
00:48:58,340 --> 00:48:59,610
But I guess this is how he did it.

563
00:49:03,449 --> 00:49:06,179
You told me that you've
never met Ha Won, right?

564
00:49:06,420 --> 00:49:09,179
No, I only saw his back from afar.

565
00:49:11,949 --> 00:49:13,289
I think you'll meet him soon.

566
00:49:13,760 --> 00:49:15,360
Or you might've met him already.

567
00:49:17,360 --> 00:49:18,389
What?

568
00:49:20,059 --> 00:49:21,099
I'm relieved.

569
00:52:00,820 --> 00:52:01,989
Is something bothering you?

570
00:52:03,489 --> 00:52:05,090
I just can't seem to focus.

571
00:52:08,329 --> 00:52:09,900
This is our last day.

572
00:52:13,469 --> 00:52:16,199
We just need to record
one more piece. Then it'll be over.

573
00:52:22,079 --> 00:52:23,349
Why did she go?

574
00:52:27,619 --> 00:52:28,949
Why did she have to go?

575
00:52:40,360 --> 00:52:42,760
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

576
00:53:29,639 --> 00:53:31,809
In Wook sure isn't himself.

577
00:54:41,650 --> 00:54:45,150
It was great. That was amazing.

578
00:57:00,050 --> 00:57:01,659
So she didn't come today either.

579
00:57:02,289 --> 00:57:03,829
I'm sure she will someday though.

580
00:57:03,829 --> 00:57:06,690
When she does,
I'll tell her how long you waited.

581
00:57:06,690 --> 00:57:08,300
I hope your patience is rewarded.

582
00:57:08,300 --> 00:57:10,000
Don't you go back on that promise.

583
00:57:10,000 --> 00:57:11,099
I won't.

584
00:57:12,699 --> 00:57:16,170
Look at the size of the moon today.
It's as if it's rolling toward us.

585
00:57:21,210 --> 00:57:22,710
Make a wish.

586
00:57:23,809 --> 00:57:25,010
It'll come true.

587
00:57:41,960 --> 00:57:43,230
Hello?

588
00:57:43,400 --> 00:57:45,030
This place...

589
00:57:45,500 --> 00:57:47,099
is blinding.

590
00:57:47,369 --> 00:57:49,199
It's amazing here.

591
00:57:51,539 --> 00:57:52,869
Now I realize...

592
00:57:52,869 --> 00:57:54,739
why I've been living my life
the way I have.

593
00:57:55,480 --> 00:57:57,079
My anxiety is gone too.

594
00:57:57,079 --> 00:57:58,449
Where are you right now?

595
00:57:59,179 --> 00:58:01,849
On the path
Ha Won and I always used to walk on.

596
00:58:02,380 --> 00:58:03,889
In Norway?

597
00:58:07,219 --> 00:58:09,619
I don't know how I managed
to forget about this place.

598
00:58:09,690 --> 00:58:12,059
Is this the normal tone
your voice carries?

599
00:58:12,059 --> 00:58:13,960
Talk about it being different.

600
00:58:14,599 --> 00:58:16,400
I'm glad you went there.

601
00:58:16,400 --> 00:58:18,530
I can handle it all, you know.

602
00:58:18,599 --> 00:58:20,599
I'm quite strong.

603
00:58:21,070 --> 00:58:23,300
I'm glad I came here
by myself though.

604
00:58:25,469 --> 00:58:27,280
Seo Woo,

605
00:58:27,280 --> 00:58:31,409
could you tell Ha Won not to wait
for me at the cafe anymore?

606
00:58:31,809 --> 00:58:33,579
I left Korea without telling him.

607
00:58:33,650 --> 00:58:37,690
Being the stubborn guy he is,
he'll keep on waiting.

608
00:58:37,690 --> 00:58:40,019
But I don't know who he is.

609
00:58:40,019 --> 00:58:41,690
The answer's easy.

610
00:58:42,389 --> 00:58:43,590
Consider it as a pop quiz.

611
00:58:43,590 --> 00:58:46,289
I'll call you in a while,
so get thinking.

612
00:58:47,829 --> 00:58:49,000
Here's a hint.

613
00:58:49,400 --> 00:58:51,400
You've already met him.

614
00:58:54,170 --> 00:58:56,139
I'll call you back.

615
00:58:56,639 --> 00:58:57,670
But...

616
00:58:59,739 --> 00:59:01,539
Who on earth is Ha Won?

617
00:59:07,019 --> 00:59:08,980
Wouldn't it be possible
if someone's that precious?

618
00:59:10,019 --> 00:59:13,690
I think it's possible if that person
is what keeps you grounded.

619
00:59:14,789 --> 00:59:16,260
No way.

620
00:59:20,400 --> 00:59:23,670
Misery found me
but I never contacted him.

621
00:59:23,829 --> 00:59:25,329
She told you
that her life is miserable?

622
00:59:30,539 --> 00:59:31,639
"I want you to stay."

623
00:59:31,639 --> 00:59:34,980
You're to be there.
You're to always be at the studio.

624
00:59:34,980 --> 00:59:37,909
You should work at the studio that
wants you to stay for a long time.

625
00:59:39,880 --> 00:59:41,920
Was that you as well?

626
